{"key":"post-13063189","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>13063189</id>\n<content>After filling your &lt;b&gt;1/2 pint jars&lt;/b&gt;, take a wooden spoon and smack the side of the jar a few times as you spin it around.&amp;nbsp; This will get the brf to settle, so you can add more before putting the verm layer on top.&amp;nbsp; If you're incorrectly using pints, don't even ask why it settled.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Also, make sure you're using fine verm, especially for the filter.&amp;nbsp; Course verm has large air spaces between it, and as it shifts, it will settle a lot more.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>13063251</next>\n<prev>13063053</prev>\n<first>13063026</first>\n<last>13063251</last>\n<when>1282057846</when>\n<utime>08/17/10 06:10 PM</utime>\n</post>"}